## Compact Instructions

<!-- WHY: Workflows have sequential state — losing the current step position is catastrophic. -->
<!-- WHY: Without this, a compacted session restarts the workflow from scratch. -->
<!-- WHY: [SOURCE: compact/prompt.ts:133-143] — Claude Code reads this section by name. -->

When summarizing this conversation, always preserve:
- The workflow name (`{{PRODUCT_SLUG}}`) and total step count
- Current step position and completion status of each prior step
- Step outputs that feed into downstream steps (the data pipeline)
- Any branching decisions made and the conditions that triggered them
- Variable state from variables.yaml that was set during execution
- Error states: which steps failed and what recovery was attempted
- Creator intent and acceptance criteria from /fill

